        <h1 class=" nomargin spdn bgcolt8">How To Start</h1>
        <div class="fullWidWithBGContainer lpdn">
            <h4>After installing this ERP, You can start as illustrated below</h4>
            <ol >
                <li class="greenFont">If you have entry persons then create their credentials in <b>AcessManagement</b> Module<br><br></li> 
                <li class="bluFnt">After creating users, create Raw Materials used in Product manufacturing<br><br></li> 
                <li class="greenFont">After creating Raw Material Create Products and Bill of Material(BOM),BOM represents the quantity of raw materials used in manufacturing a single product.<br><br></li> 
                <li class="bluFnt">After creating Products and Bill of Material(BOM), Create Production Branches or Factories(where manufacturing of product takes place) <br><br></li> 
                <li class="bluFnt">Then make opening stock entry in <i>ALL Branches Stock</i> <br><br></li> 
            </ol>
        </div>
        <h1 class=" nomargin spdn bgcolt8">Supportive Questions and Answers</h1>
        <div class="fullWidWithBGContainer lpdn">
            <h4 class="redFont nomargin nopadding">How this ERP is helpful and what can be managed?</h4>
            <ol >
                <li class="greenFont">ERP has two section <strong>Admin Section</strong> and <strong>Seller Section</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Admin Section
                            <ol>
                                <li>It is the core of ERP,this module's  dashboard has beautiful and Easy understandable interface to manage the things.Following is the list of modules exists in latest version 2.0</li>
                                <li><b>Access Management</b> or <b>User Management</b> </li>
                                <li><b>Finance Management</b></li>
                                <li><b>Stock Manager or All Branches Stock</b></li>
                                <li><b>RM Comsumption or All Branches Consumption</b></li>
                                <li><b>Production Manager</b> or <b>All Branches Production</b></li>
                                <li><b>Inward Manager</b> or <b>All Branches Purchase</b></li>
                                <li><b>All Branches Purchase</b></li>
                            </ol>    
                        </li>
                        <li>Seller Section
                        <ol>
                                <li>It is the helping module to manage the Sellers and Sale centers of the Company</li>
                            </ol>    
                        </li>
                        
                    </ol>
                </li> 
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fullWidWithBGContainer lpdn">
            <h4 class="redFont nomargin nopadding">Can admin limit the entry person from accessing all modules?</h4>
            <ol >
                <li class="greenFont">Yes of course,Global Admin can assign the permissions to the user and limit the access</li> 
            </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="fullWidWithBGContainer lpdn">
            <h4 class="nomargin nopadding redFont">Where can admin see the material's stock?</h4>
            <ol>
                <li class="greenFont">Material's stock is dependent on production branches and all branches stock is saved separately.Just click on AllBranchesStock <br><br></li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="fullWidWithBGContainer lpdn">
            <h4 class="nomargin nopadding redFont">What affects the material's stock?</h4>
            <ol>
                <li class="greenFont">Material's stock updated when RM is purchased or used in Production. Admin can update the latest stock
                    Any time by clicking on update stock button  <br><br></li>
            </ol>
        </div>
